text_trans: On Tuesday (2nd), Lee Jae myung, the leader of South Korea's largest opposition party and common democratic party, was attacked while attending an event in Busan. He was cut and bled in the neck by a man disguised as a supporter with a knife. Lee Jae myung fell to the ground and was immediately taken to the hospital for treatment. He was still conscious at the time, and the perpetrator was subdued by the police and taken to a police car on the spot.
